@startuml
' @id(DOM-DEPLOY-IAC)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
'
' Objective-side domain model of the IaC artifact /mdd-deploy generates.
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0016): the model is made ADAPTIVE to the class of
' ambiguity behind the Key Vault provisioning failure and the dev-vs-prod
' DB-SKU mismatch. Three concepts join the dialect gate:
'   - DeploymentPurpose <<gate>>: dev/staging/prod, confirmed before any
'     purpose-driven default; RECOMMENDS sizing/posture, never assumes.
'   - ResourceAccess <<gate>>: every secured store needs a named reader
'     AND writer, each with an identity and an admitted network path,
'     before the diagram is "done"; holes are surfaced, not shipped.
'   - Deployer <<principal>>: the previously-missing provisioning writer,
'     holding the data-plane write role, reaching the vault over a path
'     the posture admits.
' All gates SURFACE options; they never bake in an answer. Stereotypes
' here are documentation-only; this file carries NO security-parity
' markers (/mdd-deploy is outside the parity gate). Package label is
' slash-free (PlantUML treats / and .. as namespace separators).
'
' @desc(DOM-DEPLOY-IAC, "Objective: /mdd-deploy generates IaC under two confirmed gates plus one completeness gate. A DialectChoice (bicep|terraform, confirmed) and a DeploymentPurpose (dev|staging|prod, confirmed) BOTH gate artifact creation with no silent default (OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-DIALECT, -CONFIRM-BEFORE-ARTIFACT, -PURPOSE). DeploymentPurpose drives DB tier/redundancy, backup retention and the RECOMMENDED network/doorway posture, but only recommends — the operator confirms and secure-by-default is preserved (OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE). A ResourceAccess gate requires every secured store (Key Vault, PostgreSQL, ACR, remote state) to name a READER and a WRITER, each with an identity and a network path the posture admits, before the diagram is done; a store read-but-never-written, or a writer with no admitted path, is surfaced as a blocking question (OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-ACCESS-COMPLETE). The previously-missing Deployer principal carries the data-plane write role (Secrets Officer) reaching Key Vault over an admitted path, alongside the app's read-only Secrets User. BicepIaC and TerraformIaC still compose the identical secured topology and satisfy the same secure-by-default + migration-order invariants. The skill writes files and STOPS; it never deploys.")
title /mdd-deploy generated IaC structure (objective — adaptive gates)

class DialectChoice <<gate>> {
  value : {bicep | terraform}
  confirmed : Boolean
  rule = exactly one dialect per run
  rule = no artifact written until confirmed
  rule = no silent default
}

class DeploymentPurpose <<gate>> {
  value : {dev | staging | prod}
  confirmed : Boolean
  rule = no silent default (never assume dev- or prod-grade)
  rule = confirmed before any purpose-driven default
  drives = DB tier/redundancy, backup retention,
           RECOMMENDED network/doorway posture
  rule = RECOMMENDS only; operator confirms;
         secure-by-default vault posture preserved
}

class ResourceAccess <<gate>> {
  scope = every secured store (Key Vault, DB, ACR, remote state)
  reader = principal + identity + admitted path (runtime)
  writer = principal + identity + admitted path (provisioning)
  rule = read AND write both accounted for before "diagram done"
  rule = read-but-never-written => SURFACE blocking question
  rule = writer with no admitted path => SURFACE blocking question
  rule = surface the option (allowlist|in-VNet|tunnel); never bake one in
}

class Deployer <<principal>> {
  identity = operator or CI (whoever runs apply)
  role = Key Vault Secrets Officer (data-plane WRITE)
  reaches = vault over a network path the posture admits
}

abstract class IaCArtifact <<artifact>> {
  target = azure-container-apps (v1, only)
  generatedBy = /mdd-deploy (writes files, never deploys)
  appliedBy = operator
}
class BicepIaC <<artifact>> {
  language = Bicep (Azure-native ARM DSL)
  entrypoint = main.bicep
  structure = main.bicep + Bicep modules
  transpilesTo = ARM (Azure Resource Manager) JSON
  appliedVia = az deployment
}
class TerraformIaC <<artifact>> {
  language = Terraform HCL
  entrypoint = main.tf
  structure = main.tf + modules
  provider = azurerm
  stateBackend = remote (azurerm backend)
  appliedVia = terraform plan + apply
}

class ContainerRegistry <<Azure ACR>>
class ContainerAppsEnv <<Azure Container Apps>>
class AppRevision <<Azure Container Apps>> {
  ingress = 8080 external
  user = non-root
  env = NODE_ENV=production
}
class PostgresFlexibleServer <<Azure DB for PostgreSQL>> {
  transport = sslmode=require
  encryption = at-rest
  tier = set by DeploymentPurpose (dev: burstable;
         prod: general-purpose/HA) — surfaced, not assumed
}
class KeyVault <<Azure Key Vault>> {
  holds = every secret (Container Apps secret refs)
  networkDefaultAction = Deny
  bypass = AzureServices
}
class AzureOpenAI <<Azure OpenAI>>
class MigrationJob <<Azure Container Apps Job>> {
  order = before any revision traffic routing
}

DialectChoice "1" --> "1" IaCArtifact : selects & gates
DeploymentPurpose "1" --> "1" IaCArtifact : sizes & postures (recommends)
IaCArtifact <|-- BicepIaC
IaCArtifact <|-- TerraformIaC

IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" ContainerRegistry
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" ContainerAppsEnv
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" KeyVault
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" PostgresFlexibleServer
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" AzureOpenAI
IaCArtifact "1" *-- "1" MigrationJob
ContainerAppsEnv "1" *-- "1..*" AppRevision
AppRevision ..> ContainerRegistry : pull image
AppRevision ..> KeyVault : secret refs <<Secrets User>> (runtime READ)
AppRevision ..> PostgresFlexibleServer : <<Encrypt>> TLS (sslmode=require)
AppRevision ..> AzureOpenAI : API key (landmine: NOT managed identity)
MigrationJob ..> PostgresFlexibleServer : <<Encrypt>> schema migrate
MigrationJob "1" --> "1" AppRevision : completes BEFORE\ntraffic routing

Deployer ..> KeyVault : set secrets <<Secrets Officer>> (provisioning WRITE)
ResourceAccess "1" --> "1" KeyVault : completeness check (exemplar)

note bottom of DialectChoice
  Mandatory blocking confirmation BEFORE any deploy
  artifact. Invariants: OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-DIALECT and
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-CONFIRM-BEFORE-ARTIFACT.
end note

note bottom of DeploymentPurpose
  Mandatory blocking confirmation BEFORE any
  purpose-driven default (DB tier/redundancy, backup
  retention, recommended doorway). No silent default;
  never assume prod- or dev-grade. RECOMMENDS only —
  the operator confirms; secure-by-default vault posture
  is preserved. Invariants: OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-PURPOSE,
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SURFACE-NOT-DECIDE.
end note

note bottom of ResourceAccess
  Same read+write+admitted-path completeness applies to
  EVERY secured store — DB, ACR, remote state — not only
  Key Vault (shown as the exemplar). A store read but
  never written, or a writer with no admitted path, is
  SURFACED as a blocking question, not shipped as a
  complete-looking diagram. Invariant:
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-ACCESS-COMPLETE.
end note

note bottom of Deployer
  The previously-missing provisioning WRITER: who puts
  secrets INTO the vault at deploy time. Holds the
  data-plane Secrets Officer role and reaches the vault
  over a path the posture admits — alongside the app's
  read-only Secrets User. Modeling both is what the
  ResourceAccess completeness gate enforces.
end note

note bottom of KeyVault
  Secure-by-default, identical for BOTH dialects: when
  Postgres + Azure OpenAI are private, Key Vault is
  generated with networkAcls.defaultAction='Deny' +
  bypass='AzureServices' (or a private endpoint). Any
  relaxation to admit the writer is an explicit, surfaced
  decision. Invariant: OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SECURE-BY-DEFAULT.
end note

note bottom of IaCArtifact
  FULL PARITY: BicepIaC and TerraformIaC compose the
  same secured topology and satisfy the same invariant
  checklist; only language/structure/state differ.
  Produced by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE; written into
  CMP-DEPLOY-TARGET. Constrained by
  OCL-DEPLOY-IAC-SECURE-BY-DEFAULT / -MIGRATION-ORDER.
end note
@enduml
